───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NOTES
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
- The LLM call here is intentionally synchronous (llm.invoke), not
  streamed. The reasoning sentence is short and fits in the controller
  return path. It will appear in the chat as part of the static
  message returned by the node.
- The helper catches ALL exceptions so a flaky LLM never blocks the
  user from seeing the procedural confirmation.
- A 25-word ceiling is enforced via prompt; the helper does not
  truncate. If the LLM ignores it, the user sees a slightly longer
  sentence — not a failure.
- ENABLE_REASONING_ADDON=False in config disables all reasoning
  calls instantly; the nodes still call add_reasoning() but it
  returns the input unchanged.

